    "description": "\u003cp\u003eChemovator is the business incubator of BASF. We provide a protected space to build commercial ventures from unconventional ideas. Our Venture Teams take full ownership of their idea, creatively explore their business, learn fast and pivot beyond corporate boundaries.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVenture Team\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003esharcx\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOur Venture Team sharcx develops cloud-based analytical services which allow B2B sales and marketers to drive sales by automatically increased customer satisfaction. The data analytics engine will decrease customer churn, improve customer satisfaction (e.g. NPSÂ®) and increase the customer lifetime value. For more information, have a look at \u003ca href=\"http://www.sharcx.com/\"\u003ewww.sharcx.com\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWe now want to grow our software development stream and we are looking for a motivated and highly self-driven working student to bring our continuous delivery process to the next level. Are you the right one to join us on this journey?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat you can expect from the role\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou support our team with defining and evaluating our SDLC processes\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou identify potential for test automation and take through required steps to implement it\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou support the team with the implementation of features\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou support the team with managing bugs and the bug fixing process\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat you bring to the table\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou are currently studying (bachelorâ€™s â€“ minimum 5th semester or masterâ€™s degree) in the field of applied informatics / computer science or business informatics\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou have experience in agile software development and software testing procedures\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou have experience in C#, .NET Core and Angular\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou are interested in applying modern tools and automate the development flow\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou have experience with CI/CD tools (e.g. Jenkins, TeamCity, DevOps)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou have experience with tools for (agile) software development (e.g. Jira, Git)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat you can expect from us\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eA steady interaction and dialogue with experienced experts from two worlds â€“ corporate BASF and our wide external network\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eUse the mass of experiences of your colleagues and our Entrepreneurs in Residence to develop yourself and your venture further\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eFlexible working time and mobile work as well as usual perks of a company in the startup environment, e.g. free drinks and an inspiring atmosphere within an unconventional location in Mannheim\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eA competitive salary and the potential opportunity to join sharcx full time after you have finished your studies\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThrilled?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNothing is set in stone yet, so your input is highly welcome. Please contact Tobias Seeger with your relevant documents. We are looking forward to hearing from you!\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://camo.githubusercontent.com/71cd2f8024566adec9675d9afd1c185be08a0127/68747470733a2f2f742e676f686972696e672e636f6d2f682f65396639643839646239373562386135326634393131383662626265646436373764626565363731653862343735343634383338643238646639306139303837\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n",
